<section class="section section--safety section--rev">
    <div class="aux">
        <div class="grid grid--middle">
            <div class="section__content grid__item palm--one-whole lap--one-half desk--one-half">
                <header class="section__header">
                    <h2 class="section__title">Keep track of shared&nbsp;expenses</h2>
                    <p>Whether you’re splitting a bill, buying a group gift, or planning a trip with friends, requesting money with Google Wallet is an easy way to track who still needs to pay you back.</p>
                    <p>You can also use Google Wallet for occasional commercial transactions, like collecting rent or accepting payments for services. Just make sure you have the <a href="https://wallet.google.com/n/settings?utm_source=wallet&amp;utm_medium=website&amp;utm_campaign=website-shared-expenses&amp;authuser=0" target="_blank">commercial payments setting</a> turned on. <a href="https://support.google.com/wallet/answer/6285485?hl=en" target="_blank">Learn&nbsp;more.</a></p>
                    <p><a href="" class="basic-cta" data-g-label="" target="_blank"></a></p>
                </header>
            </div>
            <!--
            -->
            <div class="section__image grid__item palm--one-whole lap--one-half desk--one-half">
                <picture>
                    <!--[if IE 9]><video style="display: none;"><![endif]-->
                    <source srcset="../image/scissors.jpeg" media="(min-width: 481px)">
                    <source srcset="../image/scissors.jpeg" media="(max-width: 480px)">
                    <!--[if IE 9]></video><![endif]-->
                    <img srcset="../image/scissors.jpeg" alt="Keep your money safe">
